article.description: Deshaw Andrews was 5-for-5 from 3-point range and had a career-high 30 points as Alcorn State romped past Arkansas-Pine Bluff 82-54 on Monday night.
article.headline: Alcorn State shoots its way past Arkansas-Pine Bluff 82-54
article.linkText: Alcorn State shoots its way past Arkansas-Pine Bluff 82-54
article.story: PINE BLUFF, Ark. -- Deshaw Andrews was 5-for-5 from 3-point range and had a career-high 30 points as Alcorn State romped past Arkansas-Pine Bluff 82-54 on Monday night. Andrews hit 9 of 11 shots from the field and the Braves collectively were 10 of 15 from long range and 25 of 49 (51%) from the floor. Maurice Howard had 13 points and six rebounds for Alcorn State (8-9, 4-2 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Corey Tillery added 10 points. Troymain Crosby had 9 points and 11 rebounds. Artavious McDyess had 12 points for the Golden Lions (3-14, 2-3). Marquell Carter added 11 points. Alcorn State plays Alabama A&M at home on Saturday. Arkansas-Pine Bluff plays Prairie View on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
